A member of the Presidential Advisory Committee Against Corruption, Prof Isa Sadiq Raddah, has said that no fewer than 12,000 projects which part payments are made, are abandoned by the Niger Delta Development Commission (NDDC). Raddah, who is also a member of the NDDC Forensic Audit Committee, added that 1,700 contractors took mobilisation feess and vanished into the air. Speaking at a workshop in Sokoto, organised by the Network for Justice on Budget Monitoring and Tracking, Prof .Raddah divulged that before now, getting a contract in NDDC was akin to winning a ottery, adding that, however, that 76 contractors had gone back to site since the forensic auditing of contracts awarded in the NDDC began. “NDDC for 20 years has gotten over $40 billion. And when you calculate $40 billion into naira, we are talking of N116 trillion. The Dubai you have today does not even have that. The Dubai you have began with $20 billion. But look at Niger Delta where I tell you Nigeria has sunk over $40 billion. “If we had done that, the Niger Delta would have by now been the engine room for the development of not only Nigeria but even West African countries because many West African countries would have developed and benefited from the investments in Niger Delta. “But the entire money was taken away by their young people, their leaders, their agitators, their activists and now the Niger Delta is as bad as many of the rural areas you find in Northern Nigeria. Not because they don’t have the money but you can now see simply because there is corruption.